<h1>Electron</h1>

<p>Electron application development and packaging is provided in the <code>@ascua/electron</code> package. The package will install the necessary dependencies, and will create an <code>electron/main.js</code> file for the electron window code.</p>

<Example @name="demo-guides-electron-install.bash">
	ember install @ascua/electron
</Example>

<h2>Development</h2>

<p>To begin developing your Ember app as an Electron app, run the following command in your Ember app directory to begin development. To configure the electron app startup process, edit the <code>electron/main.js</code> file.</p>

<Example @name="demo-guides-electron-serve.bash">
	ember electron:serve
</Example>

<h2>Deployment</h2>

<p>When you are ready to deploy, ensure that you have correctly entered the necessary build information in your application's <code>package.json</code> file. Then run the following command in your Ember app directory to begin the ember app build and deploy process.</p>

<Example @name="demo-guides-electron-build.bash">
	ember electron:build
</Example>

<h2>Rebuild dependencies</h2>

<p>Run the following command in your application's working directory, to ensure that all dependencies are rebuilt for the current platform.</p>

<Example @name="demo-guides-electron-dependencies.bash">
	electron-builder install-app-deps
</Example>

<p>Alternatively, run this command after every npm package install, by placing it in your <code>package.json</code> file.</p>

<Example @name="demo-guides-electron-dependencies.json">
	{
	  "scripts": {
	    "postinstall": "electron-builder install-app-deps"
	  }
	}
</Example>

<h2>Example build configuration</h2>

<p>To configure the application build and deployment specify a <code>build</code> section in your <code>package.json</code> file.</p>

<Example @name="demo-guides-electron-config.json">
